# Territory Developer — Project Overview

**Language:** All code, comments, XML docs, annotations, Debug.Log messages, and repository content must be in **English**.

**Stack:** Unity 2D isometric city-builder; C# MonoBehaviour classes; `Territory.*` namespaces (partial migration); no DI — Inspector fields + `FindObjectOfType<T>()` fallback in Awake/Start.

**Folder layout (`Assets/Scripts/`):**
- `Managers/GameManagers/` (~94 files) — core game logic: grid, terrain, zones, roads, economy, simulation, helpers
- `Managers/UnitManagers/` (~64 files) — data models: Cell, Zone, Building, Forest, HeightMap, CellData, WaterMap, etc.
- `Controllers/GameControllers/` (~6 files) — CameraController, CityStatsUIController, etc.
- `Controllers/UnitControllers/` (~38 files) — UI buttons, popups, sliders
- `Utilities/` (~6 files) — DebugHelper, RoadPathCostConstants, etc.

**Key facts:** GridManager is the central hub for cell operations. Only singleton: `GameNotificationManager.Instance`. Data models: MonoBehaviour-based (Cell, Zone on GameObjects) vs plain classes (CellData, CommuneData, TerritoryData for serialization). Grid uses `Cell[,] cellArray` + `GameObject[,] gridArray` with heightMap-based isometric height system.

**Style reference:** `EconomyManager.cs` (XML docs + `#region` + `[Header]` attributes).

**Deep architecture / deps / flows:** `ARCHITECTURE.md`. **Geography:** `.cursor/specs/isometric-geography-system.md` (spec §7 for sorting order).
